commands.name: az network dns record-set ds add-record
commands.syntax:
az network dns record-set ds add-record --algorithm
                                        --digest
                                        --digest-type
                                        --key-tag
                                        --record-set-name
                                        --resource-group
                                        --zone-name
                                        [--if-none-match]
                                        [--ttl]
examples:
az network dns record-set ds add-record -g MyResourceGroup -z www.mysite.com \
    -n MyRecordSet --algorithm 3 --digest "49FD46E6C4B45C55D4AC" --digest-type 1 --key-tag 12345

commands.name: az network dns record-set ds create
commands.syntax:
az network dns record-set ds create --name
                                    --resource-group
                                    --zone-name
                                    [--if-match]
                                    [--if-none-match]
                                    [--metadata]
                                    [--target-resource]
                                    [--tm-profile]
                                    [--ttl]
examples: az network dns record-set ds create -g MyResourceGroup -z www.mysite.com -n MyRecordSet --metadata owner=WebTeam

commands.name: az network dns record-set ds delete
commands.syntax:
az network dns record-set ds delete [--ids]
                                    [--if-match]
                                    [--name]
                                    [--resource-group]
                                    [--subscription]
                                    [--yes]
                                    [--zone-name]
examples: az network dns record-set ds delete -g MyResourceGroup -z www.mysite.com -n MyRecordSet

commands.name: az network dns record-set ds list
commands.summary: List DS record sets in a zone.
commands.syntax:
az network dns record-set ds list --resource-group
                                  --zone-name
                                  [--max-items]
                                  [--next-token]
                                  [--recordsetnamesuffix]
                                  [--top]
examples: az network dns record-set ds list -g MyResourceGroup -z www.mysite.com

commands.name: az network dns record-set ds remove-record
commands.summary: Remove a DS record from its record set.
commands.syntax:
az network dns record-set ds remove-record --algorithm
                                           --digest
                                           --digest-type
                                           --key-tag
                                           --record-set-name
                                           --resource-group
                                           --zone-name
                                           [--keep-empty-record-set]
examples:
az network dns record-set ds remove-record -g MyResourceGroup -z www.mysite.com \
    -n MyRecordSet --algorithm 3 --digest "49FD46E6C4B45C55D4AC" --digest-type 1 --key-tag 12345

commands.name: az network dns record-set ds show
commands.syntax:
az network dns record-set ds show [--ids]
                                  [--name]
                                  [--resource-group]
                                  [--subscription]
                                  [--zone-name]
examples: az network dns record-set ds show -g MyResourceGroup -z www.mysite.com -n MyRecordSet

commands.name: az network dns record-set ds update
commands.syntax:
az network dns record-set ds update [--add]
                                    [--force-string {0, 1, f, false, n, no, t, true, y, yes}]
                                    [--ids]
                                    [--if-match]
                                    [--if-none-match]
                                    [--metadata]
                                    [--name]
                                    [--remove]
                                    [--resource-group]
                                    [--set]
                                    [--subscription]
                                    [--target-resource]
                                    [--tm-profile]
                                    [--zone-name]
examples: az network dns record-set ds update -g MyResourceGroup -z www.mysite.com -n MyRecordSet --metadata owner=WebTeam
